            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "The physical education teacher cannot even do a push-up let alone teach the students how to. PE / PT Teacher shows up in class and just talks to himself while grinding a piece of chalk on the table. Physical education is not taken seriously. The Arts teacher does not let the students go home even after school hours are over. He holds them hostage. The teachers in general give preferential treatment to local kids above the rest. The teachers get one of the students to teach and get busy on their mobile phones. The School Principal is careless and does not bother about the children's health and safety, but busy doing cost cutting and scams. If the school offers children food on Diwali or for any occasion, please ask your children not to consume the food. The staff will procure the food from unhygienic sources to cut costs. This school has already faced a situation whereby after giving unhealthy food to kids on Diwali, several children got admitted in hospital with gastric issues. Parents give an innocent child to this school, after 10 years the school has successfully turned the child into a delinquent.",
